The paper discusses schedulers for a class of rules in the context of rule-based constraint programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the implementation of these rules, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the identification of redundant rules, which is related to logic and verification (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the computation of reduced sets of rules, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
